WEBVTT

00:18.152 --> 00:19.620
- It's every kid's dream.

00:19.687 --> 00:21.822
A snowstorm hits a town
so hard

00:21.889 --> 00:24.758
that all the roads
are completely undriveable.

00:24.825 --> 00:27.361
- All right, hold on,
Mr. Narrator Guy.

00:27.428 --> 00:28.496
I'll take it from here.

00:28.562 --> 00:30.531
- Uh, okay.

00:30.598 --> 00:33.033
- As he was saying,
sometimes a snowstorm

00:33.101 --> 00:37.138
is so big that school is
canceled for the whole day.

00:37.205 --> 00:39.340
It's a surprise vacation,

00:39.407 --> 00:41.675
a "get out of class free"
card,

00:41.742 --> 00:45.846
a magical, fun day
where anything can happen.

00:46.580 --> 00:48.616
A snow day.

00:48.682 --> 00:50.551
- And now let's turn it over
to Deborah May

00:50.618 --> 00:52.520
for traffic
and weather together.

00:52.586 --> 00:54.288
- Hello, Syracuse!

00:54.355 --> 00:55.656
Our top story today

00:55.723 --> 00:57.725
is that mountain
of snow outside your door.

00:57.791 --> 01:00.094
- You see that darling,
wide-eyed girl?

01:00.161 --> 01:03.297
That's me, Natalie Brandston,
one year ago.

01:03.364 --> 01:05.366
Boy, was I cute!

01:05.432 --> 01:07.101
And next to me

01:07.168 --> 01:10.037
is my charmingly
awkward brother, Hal.

01:10.104 --> 01:11.905
- Undriveable.

01:11.972 --> 01:14.942
I mean, I was lucky to get
out of my garage before it--

01:15.008 --> 01:17.345
- But back to me.
Why do I look nervous?

01:17.411 --> 01:20.381
Because I had a big, old
English paper due that day,

01:20.448 --> 01:22.650
and I hadn't even started.

01:22.716 --> 01:25.953
- I am just getting word
that due to road closures,

01:26.019 --> 01:28.055
all Syracuse schools
will be closed...

01:29.657 --> 01:31.425
