03:35.416 --> 03:37.385
with a high of 65 degrees.

03:37.451 --> 03:39.987
- Well, here I am one year
later, still cute,

03:40.053 --> 03:42.555
but unfortunately, no snow.

03:42.623 --> 03:44.024
- Here's a fun fact.

03:44.091 --> 03:45.826
On this exact date last year,

03:45.893 --> 03:47.828
Syracuse had a snow day.

03:47.895 --> 03:50.798
- There's nothing fun
about that fact, Deborah.

03:50.864 --> 03:53.033
Hal, you got to help me.

03:53.100 --> 03:54.502
Winter break is in
three days,

03:54.567 --> 03:56.804
and I need to get
out of school until then.

03:56.870 --> 03:58.506
- How come?
- To get out of all the tests

03:58.572 --> 04:00.040
I refuse to study for!

04:00.107 --> 04:03.477
Right now, I have
a perfect 70% average.

04:03.544 --> 04:05.178
Any dips and it's--
- Winter school?

04:05.245 --> 04:06.947
- Winter school.
- Oh, no.

04:07.014 --> 04:08.148
- Oh, yes.

04:08.215 --> 04:09.683
Summer school's
even more evil twin.

04:09.750 --> 04:11.352
When you leave at
the end of the day,

04:11.419 --> 04:12.920
it's dark and depressing.

04:12.986 --> 04:14.388
And while all
the other kids

04:14.455 --> 04:16.255
are playing with the things
they got for Christmas,

04:16.324 --> 04:18.358
you've got homework.

04:18.426 --> 04:20.260
[suspenseful music]

04:20.327 --> 04:22.029
- Okay, Mom's putting
on her second shoe,

04:22.095 --> 04:23.664
so we don't have a lot of time.

04:23.731 --> 04:24.932
- You and your
freakish hearing.

04:24.998 --> 04:26.367
- Yeah, that's my superpower.

04:26.434 --> 04:27.635
- It's not a superpower.

04:27.701 --> 04:29.102
Nobody would go see
the movie "Ear Man."

04:29.169 --> 04:31.038
- Okay, if you don't
want my help--

04:31.104 --> 04:33.607
- No, the world needs
Ear Man now, more than ever.

04:33.674 --> 04:35.909
- Okay, okay, uh...
have a stuffed doze.

04:35.976 --> 04:38.145
- Doze?
- Doze, like nose.

04:38.211 --> 04:39.713
And instead of
saying the letter M,

04:39.780 --> 04:41.315
say the letter B.

04:41.382 --> 04:44.652
It'll bake it sound like your
doze is clogged with bucus.

04:44.718 --> 04:46.787
- You're good.
Why don't you ever fake sick?

04:46.854 --> 04:48.556
- Oh, no, I'm just
the ideas guy.

04:48.622 --> 04:50.924
I don't do so hot
with the actual doing.

04:50.991 --> 04:53.361
- He's got above average
hearing and good ideas,

04:53.427 --> 04:54.928
but no follow-through.

04:54.995 --> 04:59.332
Coming this spring, Ear Man,
the anti-action hero.

04:59.400 --> 05:01.201
- I'd see it.

05:02.836 --> 05:04.805
Showtime.
- Okay.

05:04.872 --> 05:06.374
- Time for school, guys.

05:06.440 --> 05:09.343
- Bob, is that you?

05:09.410 --> 05:11.211
- Who's Bob?

05:11.278 --> 05:14.648
- Sorry, it's my nose,
totally clogged with bucus,

05:14.715 --> 05:16.617
which I'm sure you can hear.

05:16.684 --> 05:18.218
- Sounds pretty bad, huh?

05:18.285 --> 05:19.953
- Actually, it sounds like
somebody's trying to

05:20.020 --> 05:21.789
get out of all of her tests
the next three days

05:21.855 --> 05:24.124
so she doesn't have to
go to winter school.

05:26.226 --> 05:30.297
Ear Man gets his above average
hearing from Ear Mom.

05:30.364 --> 05:33.066
Now, that's a movie I'd see.

05:33.133 --> 05:34.234
- Phew.

05:34.301 --> 05:35.469
You'll figure
something else out.

05:35.536 --> 05:37.471
- Good morning, family.

05:37.538 --> 05:39.172
- Hey, Dad.
- Morning, Dad.

05:39.239 --> 05:41.542
- I am Cop-o-dile,

05:41.609 --> 05:46.213
half cop, half croc,
all business.

05:46.279 --> 05:47.581
[whispers] Okay,
go steal something,

05:47.648 --> 05:49.483
and then I'll bite you
in the name of justice.

05:49.550 --> 05:52.252
- Sorry, Randy, I don't have
time to play with you today.

05:52.319 --> 05:53.954
- Why not?

05:54.021 --> 05:57.791
- Because like the
mighty croc, I'm swamped.

05:59.058 --> 06:00.227
- [sighs]

06:00.293 --> 06:02.129
- Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, Randy.

06:02.195 --> 06:04.565
Did you know that the crocodile
releases heat

06:04.632 --> 06:07.568
through his mouth because
he doesn't have sweat glands?

06:07.635 --> 06:09.703
- Ugh.

06:09.770 --> 06:11.405
- It's a fun fact.

06:11.472 --> 06:14.442
- Do no adults understand
the meaning of fun fact?

06:14.508 --> 06:17.310
[phone buzzes]
- Oh, yes!

06:17.377 --> 06:19.613
The spotlight operator for the
winter dance recital is sick.

06:19.680 --> 06:21.348
- With what?
Something contagious?

06:21.415 --> 06:22.816
I will lick him.

06:22.883 --> 06:24.952
- It means I get to run
the spotlight after school.

06:25.018 --> 06:27.721
- Why are you so excited
about running the spotlight?

06:27.788 --> 06:30.290
- What?

06:30.357 --> 06:31.692
No reason.

06:31.759 --> 06:33.894
No, I--I just love
the craft...

06:33.961 --> 06:37.264
of light...spotting.

06:43.370 --> 06:45.172
- It's a girl.

06:45.238 --> 06:48.408
["Dance of the Sugar
Plum Fairy"]

06:48.476 --> 06:55.415
* *

07:07.294 --> 07:08.496
- Oh!

07:08.562 --> 07:10.097
[laughing] Lane.

07:10.163 --> 07:12.299
Oh, I seriously think you just
shaved a year off of my life.

07:12.365 --> 07:13.834
- It wasn't going
to be a great year.

07:13.901 --> 07:15.235
I checked.
- Ha ha.

07:15.302 --> 07:16.269
- Here.

07:16.336 --> 07:18.138
- Oh, thank you.

07:18.205 --> 07:21.441
* *

07:21.509 --> 07:22.910
[squealing]

07:22.976 --> 07:25.145
- That was lovely, Claire.
All right.

07:25.212 --> 07:27.414
My dancers on stage
can take a break.

07:27.481 --> 07:29.149
We're moving on to
the nondenominational

07:29.216 --> 07:30.417
winter dance.

07:30.484 --> 07:33.220
- Don't you get bored
all alone up here?

07:33.286 --> 07:34.287
- No way.

07:34.354 --> 07:36.256
No, this is like
my perfect job.

07:36.323 --> 07:37.525
I get to shine
a light on the stage,

07:37.591 --> 07:39.126
but stay in the shadows.

07:39.192 --> 07:41.261
I control the spotlight,
but I'm out of it.

07:41.328 --> 07:42.596
- How poetic.

07:42.663 --> 07:44.532
- Plus, I can stare at
Claire all rehearsal,

07:44.598 --> 07:45.666
and it's not weird.

07:45.733 --> 07:46.734
- How pathetic.

07:46.800 --> 07:48.135
- Mittens, can you come--

07:48.201 --> 07:50.270
no, left.
You're on the left.

07:50.337 --> 07:51.104
No, you're on the--

07:51.171 --> 07:52.606
all right, all right!

07:52.673 --> 07:55.576
You're mittens, not gloves!

07:55.643 --> 07:57.077
I need a five.

07:57.745 --> 07:58.912
- [chuckles]

07:58.979 --> 08:01.782
[indistinct chatter]

08:03.884 --> 08:07.955
- Well, as riveting as it is to
watch you watch Claire Bonner,

08:08.021 --> 08:10.624
I think I saw some
paint drying outside.

08:10.691 --> 08:12.325
So got to get to that.

08:12.392 --> 08:13.694
- Hey, you want
to grab some food

08:13.761 --> 08:14.862
when I'm out of rehearsal?

08:14.928 --> 08:17.698
- I do, but first...
[snaps] shoes.

08:17.765 --> 08:19.032
Lift.

08:19.099 --> 08:21.368
Who am I?
- You're my hero.

08:21.434 --> 08:23.236
- You know, I don't like
you being up so high,

08:23.303 --> 08:26.306
considering you're, shall
we say, less than graceful.

08:26.373 --> 08:28.576
I mean, you do tend
to fall a lot when--

08:28.642 --> 08:29.577
- Shh, shh, Claire's talking.

08:29.643 --> 08:31.779
- [gasp] She is?

08:31.845 --> 08:33.480
Hold on.

08:33.547 --> 08:35.549
Hi, TMZ?
Hot goss.

08:35.616 --> 08:37.717
Claire Bonner is talking.

08:37.784 --> 08:39.052
No, I'm 100%--

08:39.119 --> 08:41.054
- Okay, okay, go watch
your paint dry.

08:41.121 --> 08:42.722
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
[giggles]

08:42.789 --> 08:45.025
- And that is why turtlenecks
will never go out of fashion.

08:45.092 --> 08:46.493
- She makes
a compelling argument.

08:46.560 --> 08:49.462
- Yeah, but all I think
about is the poor turtle

08:49.529 --> 08:50.931
who had to die to make it.

08:50.998 --> 08:52.099
- No, Missy.
- Missy, you don't seriously--

08:52.165 --> 08:53.701
- No, okay, but,
like, do you think

08:53.767 --> 08:58.305
a turtleneck would hide
or accentuate, you know...

08:58.371 --> 08:59.640
my short neck?

08:59.707 --> 09:01.108
[gasp] Oh, my gosh!

09:01.174 --> 09:02.743
- What?
- My whale necklace is gone.

09:02.810 --> 09:04.878
- Okay, well, where's the last
place you remember wearing it?

09:04.945 --> 09:06.546
- Oh, probably around her neck.

09:06.614 --> 09:08.649
- Missy, I worry about you.
- No, Missy.

09:08.716 --> 09:10.851
- Okay, I'm back
and I am calm now.

09:10.918 --> 09:12.519
So let's take
this from the top.

09:12.586 --> 09:14.755
- I haven't taken that necklace
off since my dad got it for me

09:14.822 --> 09:16.590
in Barcelona five years ago.

09:16.657 --> 09:19.026
- Wow, this is like as bad
as it gets for incredibly

09:19.092 --> 09:20.493
beautiful teenage girls.

09:20.560 --> 09:22.029
- Yeah!

09:22.095 --> 09:25.332
Plus it distracts from,
you know...

09:25.398 --> 09:26.900
my short neck!

09:26.967 --> 09:28.501
- Mm.
- Mm.

09:28.568 --> 09:30.103
- Your neck is perfect.

09:30.170 --> 09:32.572
- No, you're on the--
hey, what's going on?

09:32.640 --> 09:35.208
- Oh, uh, sorry, every--ahh!

09:35.275 --> 09:36.209
[gasping]

09:38.578 --> 09:42.182
[uneasy music]

09:42.249 --> 09:43.383
Ugh.

09:43.450 --> 09:45.886
- There he is.

09:46.654 --> 09:48.889
You're lucky this
Abominable Snowman costume

09:48.956 --> 09:50.590
broke your fall.

09:50.658 --> 09:52.459
Let me get a look at you.

09:54.962 --> 09:56.529
I think he's having a seizure.

09:56.596 --> 09:59.199
Is anyone here a doctor?
- We're kids!

10:00.233 --> 10:02.402
- I'm fine.
I-'m-I'm fine.

10:02.469 --> 10:04.037
- All right, out of
my way, out of my way.

10:04.104 --> 10:05.338
Next of kin,
keeper of the will.

10:05.405 --> 10:06.940
- Nat, what are you doing here?

10:07.007 --> 10:08.241
- I'm your emergency contact.

10:08.308 --> 10:09.409
- What are you doing here?

10:09.476 --> 10:10.844
I let you out
of second period

10:10.911 --> 10:12.512
because you said
you had a tapeworm.

10:12.579 --> 10:15.248
- Jen, if you want to send
me to Principal Baker,

10:15.315 --> 10:18.051
I'd be happy to show him
the website

10:18.118 --> 10:20.587
where you sell
stolen school supplies.

10:20.654 --> 10:21.722
[school bell rings]

10:21.789 --> 10:23.090
- [huffs, laughs]

10:23.156 --> 10:26.059
- Ugh. Hey, why are you
my emergency contact

10:26.126 --> 10:27.427
and not Mom or Dad?

10:27.494 --> 10:29.029
- I changed it in the
school's computer system

10:29.096 --> 10:30.397
so I have an excuse
to ditch class

10:30.463 --> 10:32.032
every time you do
something clutzy

10:32.099 --> 10:33.633
and hurt yourself, which--

10:33.701 --> 10:35.135
let's be real, babe, is often.

10:35.202 --> 10:36.203
Ha!
- Truth.

10:36.269 --> 10:37.871
Up top.
- Woo!

10:37.938 --> 10:39.740
- Natalie Brandston,
are you jumping?

10:39.807 --> 10:41.909
I let you out of a Spanish
test today because

10:41.975 --> 10:43.243
you said you had a hernia.

10:47.647 --> 10:49.082
- Uhh...

10:50.517 --> 10:52.252
[clears throat]

10:53.086 --> 10:54.654
- How many teachers do
you have blackmailed?

10:54.722 --> 10:57.157
- No such thing as blackmail
among friends.

10:57.224 --> 10:59.092
- Natalie Brandston.

10:59.159 --> 11:02.462
- Ms. Reynolds, to what
do I owe the pleasure?

11:02.529 --> 11:03.897
- Just thought I would
remind you

11:03.964 --> 11:05.665
of your math test tomorrow.

11:05.733 --> 11:07.634
- Oh, I wouldn't miss it!

11:07.701 --> 11:09.903
I mean, unless a distant
relative died suddenly,

11:09.970 --> 11:11.638
or I contracted
mad cow disease.

11:11.705 --> 11:14.107
- Listen, I know how you
intimidate the other teachers.

11:14.174 --> 11:15.909
There's even a Natalie
Brandston support group

11:15.976 --> 11:17.277
that meets at lunch.

11:17.344 --> 11:19.412
But it's not going
to work on me.

11:19.479 --> 11:21.214
You're taking
that test tomorrow.

11:21.281 --> 11:22.983
If you fail, I'll see you
in winter school.

11:23.050 --> 11:25.986
And we'll add,
subtract, multiply,

11:26.053 --> 11:28.521
and divide
until the sun goes down.

11:30.157 --> 11:31.524
- Why didn't you
blackmail Ms. Reynolds?

11:31.591 --> 11:32.793
- Because I got nothing.

11:32.860 --> 11:33.927
Reynolds is mean,
but she's clean.

11:33.994 --> 11:34.995
You know what I need?

11:35.062 --> 11:36.797
- Uh, to study?
- Ew! No.

11:36.864 --> 11:38.265
I need a snow day.

11:38.331 --> 11:39.266
- Nat, I don't
think we're getting

11:39.332 --> 11:40.801
a snow day anytime soon.

11:40.868 --> 11:43.937
Rebecca Menderson is
officially #Rebeccamending

11:44.004 --> 11:45.438
wearing shorts tomorrow.

11:45.505 --> 11:47.941
- I am officially
#Rebeccamending

11:48.008 --> 11:49.042
wearing shorts tomorrow.

11:49.109 --> 11:50.543
- See?

11:50.610 --> 11:51.845
- Desperate times call
for desperate measures.

11:51.912 --> 11:53.246
We got to do the snow dance.

11:53.313 --> 11:54.547
- The snow dance?
- No, we're not doing

11:54.614 --> 11:56.249
the snow dance.
- Aha! I don't think

11:56.316 --> 11:57.885
I've ever seen you dance.

11:57.951 --> 11:59.186
- Well, and that
streak shall continue.

11:59.252 --> 12:01.221
- Hal, the snow dance works.
- No, it doesn't.

12:01.288 --> 12:03.056
