24:19.158 --> 24:20.660
[giggling]

24:20.727 --> 24:23.362
- In addition to supermarkets
and convenience stores,

24:23.429 --> 24:25.331
all gas stations
are also closed

24:25.397 --> 24:28.067
due to last night's
unprecedented snowstorm.

24:28.134 --> 24:29.769
When I woke up
and looked out the window,

24:29.836 --> 24:31.170
I thought I was dreaming.

24:31.237 --> 24:33.305
I mean,
I went to bed in shorts.

24:33.372 --> 24:35.575
- Nobody asked for your
life story, Deborah.

24:35.642 --> 24:37.476
Give the people what they want!

24:37.544 --> 24:41.413
- Oh, and all
schools are canceled.

24:41.480 --> 24:42.749
Happy snow day!

24:42.815 --> 24:44.651
- Snow day!

24:44.717 --> 24:46.285
- Uhh--

24:46.352 --> 24:48.988
- ...Daaay!

24:50.523 --> 24:52.124
We did it!
- We did it.

24:52.191 --> 24:53.826
[laughter]

24:53.893 --> 24:56.128
Blank canvas.

24:56.195 --> 24:57.463
My sign.

24:57.530 --> 24:59.031
I'm Snow Day Hal.

24:59.098 --> 25:01.500
- Welcome, Snow Day Hal!
So what's first?

25:01.568 --> 25:04.771
Skiing, ice fishing,
skiing while ice fishing?

25:04.837 --> 25:06.639
- Actually,
I'm gonna spend today

25:06.706 --> 25:08.608
trying to get the girl
who's way out of my league

25:08.675 --> 25:10.042
and has a boyfriend.

25:10.109 --> 25:11.611
- That's my swaggy brother.

25:11.678 --> 25:14.113
- And hey, you have a full day
to study for that math test.

25:14.180 --> 25:16.448
- No, I have a full day to
get us a second snow day.

25:16.515 --> 25:18.050
And then it's winter break.

25:18.117 --> 25:19.952
- Okay, well, how do you plan
on getting a second snow day?

25:20.019 --> 25:21.120
If it stops snowing,

25:21.187 --> 25:22.689
these roads
are going to get cleared,

25:22.755 --> 25:24.957
and that means everything will
open back up again tomorrow,

25:25.024 --> 25:26.425
including school.

25:26.492 --> 25:28.861
- Not if I stop the guy
who plows the roads.

25:28.928 --> 25:30.096
[ominous music]

25:30.162 --> 25:32.665
- Stop Snowplowman?

25:32.732 --> 25:34.133
You know, but he's a maniac.

25:34.200 --> 25:37.136
[honking]
- Move it! Get outta the way!

25:37.203 --> 25:38.938
- I heard he drinks
wolf blood before plowing

25:39.005 --> 25:40.439
to get into beast mode.

25:40.506 --> 25:41.908
And that he ripped the braces
off the last kid

25:41.974 --> 25:43.109
who tried to stop him

25:43.175 --> 25:44.443
and turned them
into brass knuckles.

25:44.510 --> 25:46.278
- Well, lucky for me,
I have perfect teeth.

25:46.345 --> 25:48.247
Plus, anything can
happen on a snow day.

25:48.314 --> 25:51.550
- Nat, going after
Snowplowman is kinda insane.

25:51.618 --> 25:53.385
- Says the guy
who's going after the girl

25:53.452 --> 25:56.322
who's way out of his league
and has a boyfriend.

25:57.857 --> 25:58.791
- Take him down, sis.

25:58.858 --> 26:00.860
- Get the girl, bro.

26:02.428 --> 26:03.996
Hey, Hal.

26:04.063 --> 26:06.733
If we get a second snow day,
wanna spend it together?

26:06.799 --> 26:08.367
- That's a deal.

26:18.410 --> 26:19.679
- Hi. Ha.

26:19.746 --> 26:21.881
- Hello, darling.
Eli and Wayne are in the fort.

26:21.948 --> 26:23.115
- Oh, I'm sorry.

26:23.182 --> 26:25.051
I didn't realize
Eli had a sister.

26:25.117 --> 26:27.119
- [laughs] Oh, Natalie.

26:27.186 --> 26:28.621
[video sounds]
- Die, werewolf, die!

26:28.688 --> 26:29.756
- I'm losing, Elf Boy!

26:29.822 --> 26:30.857
- Move!

26:30.923 --> 26:32.291
- What are you bozos doing?

26:32.358 --> 26:33.893
- We're playing
this marvelous video game

26:33.960 --> 26:35.461
wherein one attempts
to ward off werewolves

26:35.527 --> 26:36.829
whilst building a shack.

26:36.896 --> 26:39.165
- It's called Werewolf Shack.
- Care to play?

26:39.231 --> 26:40.432
- Hey!
- Hey!

26:40.499 --> 26:42.234
- Hey, yourselves!

26:42.301 --> 26:44.837
Don't you guys realize that
today is no ordinary day?

26:44.904 --> 26:46.038
Today's a snow day.

26:46.105 --> 26:47.940
That means anything can happen.

26:48.007 --> 26:49.709
We can do anything we want.

26:49.776 --> 26:51.043
So do you wanna
spend the day

26:51.110 --> 26:52.444
taking down lame,
fake werewolves,

26:52.511 --> 26:54.146
or do you wanna
spend the day

26:54.213 --> 26:56.415
taking down
someone scary and real?

26:56.482 --> 26:57.416
- Like who?

26:57.483 --> 26:58.885
- Snowplowman.

26:58.951 --> 27:00.853
[gasping]
- Snowplowman?

27:00.920 --> 27:03.022
But he's a maniac.

27:03.089 --> 27:05.958
I heard a man once
made fun of his snow plow,

27:06.025 --> 27:07.960
so he plowed
the chap's motorcar.

27:08.027 --> 27:10.529
- Listen.
If we take down Snowplowman,

27:10.596 --> 27:11.964
we get a second snow day.

27:12.031 --> 27:13.866
- No, that's way too dangerous.

27:13.933 --> 27:15.567
- Well, if we don't try,

27:15.634 --> 27:17.203
then you guys
won't see me all break,

27:17.269 --> 27:18.771
because I'll be
in winter school.

27:18.838 --> 27:19.772
- Nonsense, my queen.

27:19.839 --> 27:21.007
I fight with you.
- Great.

27:21.073 --> 27:22.308
You in, Wayne?

27:22.374 --> 27:23.442
- Does this answer
your question?

27:23.509 --> 27:25.011
Yeah!

27:25.077 --> 27:26.979
- Who are we taking down?

27:27.046 --> 27:30.049
all: Snowplowman!

27:30.116 --> 27:31.350
[computer chime]

27:31.417 --> 27:34.653
- Freeze!
This is Sheriff Randy.

27:34.721 --> 27:37.957
You better not steal
something, or I got you, babe.

27:38.024 --> 27:39.425
- Oh, okay.

27:39.491 --> 27:40.893
- [whispering]
Steal something!

27:40.960 --> 27:42.829
- Uh, Sheriff, well, I can't.

27:42.895 --> 27:44.263
I'm working.

27:44.330 --> 27:47.199
- But do you believe
in play after work?

27:47.266 --> 27:49.401
- No, it's a snow day, people.

27:49.468 --> 27:52.071
- Well, it's not a snow day
for mommies and daddies.

27:52.138 --> 27:53.873
We still have to work.
Sorry, bud.

27:53.940 --> 27:55.775
- Okay.

27:55.842 --> 27:57.744
- What am I doing with
these taxes right here?

27:57.810 --> 28:00.713
[clicking sound]
Oh, uh, Randy, what did I say?

28:00.780 --> 28:03.415
I was working, right?
Remember, I just said that?

28:03.482 --> 28:06.318
- You have the right
to remain silent.

28:06.385 --> 28:08.687
- Oh, very funny.
But--

28:08.755 --> 28:11.958
- Bet you wish you could
turn back time now.

28:12.024 --> 28:13.359
- Sheriff, we appreciate--

28:13.425 --> 28:14.894
- Sorry.
- That you are

28:14.961 --> 28:18.030
a musical officer of the law
and that we're being no fun,

28:18.097 --> 28:19.365
but we really do have to work.
So...

28:19.431 --> 28:20.599
- Ow.

28:20.666 --> 28:21.801
- If you could take
these off, please?

28:21.868 --> 28:23.502
- Yeah, I mean we have to
meet our deadline

28:23.569 --> 28:25.704
so that we can
make money to buy you,

28:25.772 --> 28:29.809
you know, hats and wigs
and badges and water guns.

28:29.876 --> 28:31.643
- Hand over the devices.

28:31.710 --> 28:33.312
- No, come on.
- Yes.

28:33.379 --> 28:35.581
- My computer?
- Yes.

28:35.647 --> 28:37.016
- All right, fine,
but that's it.

28:37.083 --> 28:39.585
I need to use my phone.
- And the phones.

28:39.651 --> 28:41.420
Come on.

28:41.487 --> 28:42.755
All of them.

28:42.822 --> 28:43.890
- That's all we have.

28:43.956 --> 28:45.792
[phone rings]

28:45.858 --> 28:47.026
Where was that one?

28:47.093 --> 28:48.360
Okay, you have
all of our stuff.

28:48.427 --> 28:51.397
Now can you please uncuff us?

28:51.463 --> 28:54.000
- Not until I have
the perfect snow day.

28:54.066 --> 28:56.335
And first, I want
the perfect pancakes.

28:56.402 --> 28:57.937
- [scoffs]
- No, w--

28:58.004 --> 29:01.073
- Kinda hard to do that when
you're handcuffed together.

29:01.140 --> 29:02.574
- Yeah.

29:02.641 --> 29:06.212
- Then I suppose you'll
have to make them together.

29:08.547 --> 29:09.982
- Oh! Hoo!

29:10.049 --> 29:11.483
[laughter]

29:11.550 --> 29:12.484
- Ah!

29:12.551 --> 29:14.653
- Come here!

29:14.720 --> 29:17.223
- Okay, let's beat the rush
to the rink--come on.

29:17.289 --> 29:18.858
- Oh, I can't.
- Why not?

29:18.925 --> 29:20.626
- Well, because
I'm Snow Day Hal,

29:20.692 --> 29:22.962
and I can't let whatever
comes over me on a snow day

29:23.029 --> 29:24.596
go to waste, so...

29:24.663 --> 29:26.265
I'm gonna get Claire.

29:26.332 --> 29:27.566
- Oh.
Hm.

29:27.633 --> 29:29.468
- What?
- No, nothing, I just--

29:29.535 --> 29:31.070
I thought
I'd be spending the snow day

29:31.137 --> 29:33.105
with my best friend,
which is exactly

29:33.172 --> 29:35.007
what I'm gonna do,
'cause you need

29:35.074 --> 29:36.475
all the help you can get.

29:36.542 --> 29:38.777
- You're my hero.
- No lies detected.

29:38.845 --> 29:40.779
Now, let's see the plan.

29:40.847 --> 29:41.814
- The plan?

29:41.881 --> 29:43.782
- Hal, I know you.

29:43.850 --> 29:46.218
You have a handwritten plan
complete with funny drawings

29:46.285 --> 29:47.887
somewhere on you.

29:47.954 --> 29:49.721
Let's see it.

29:49.788 --> 29:52.091
- [sighs]
Fine.

29:54.093 --> 29:56.362
- [reading]

29:56.428 --> 29:57.763
Wait, why by sundown?
- Well, because

29:57.830 --> 29:59.365
it's a snow day.
When the sun goes down,

29:59.431 --> 30:00.933
it'll be a snow night,
and that's not a thing.

30:01.000 --> 30:03.302
- So what's the first step?
Wear this really cool sweater?

30:03.369 --> 30:05.437
- Hey, I like this sweater.

30:05.504 --> 30:07.173
- Oh ho ho.
I'm aware you do.

30:07.239 --> 30:09.675
- No, first step,
make an impression.

30:09.741 --> 30:13.412
I'm going to go to her
house and hold this up.

30:15.781 --> 30:17.449
- I don't get it.

30:17.516 --> 30:19.818
- What?
Whale you, like...

30:19.886 --> 30:21.020
like
will you go out with me?

30:21.087 --> 30:22.321
Only it's whale you
go out with me

30:22.388 --> 30:23.489
because of the whale necklace.

30:23.555 --> 30:25.224
Man, I thought that was clear.

30:25.291 --> 30:28.127
- [laughs]
I'm messing with you.

30:28.194 --> 30:29.128
It's whale-y good.

30:29.195 --> 30:30.662
- Whale-y?

30:30.729 --> 30:31.797
- Would I say "whale-y"
if I didn't whale-y,

30:31.864 --> 30:32.831
whale-y mean it?

30:32.899 --> 30:34.200
[laughs]

30:35.634 --> 30:37.569
- Yeah, okay, that's her house.

30:37.636 --> 30:39.238
- Good luck.
- Hey, Snow Day Hal

30:39.305 --> 30:40.772
doesn't need luck.
- Yeah.

30:40.839 --> 30:43.375
[engine roaring]

30:43.442 --> 30:45.978
- Okay, maybe a little luck.

30:46.045 --> 30:47.579
Go, go, go.

30:56.622 --> 31:00.326
- Claire Bear,
I have something to say!

31:02.028 --> 31:03.429
- What is it, Chuck?

31:03.495 --> 31:04.796
Are you going to miss
my birthday next year

31:04.863 --> 31:06.198
for a toast convention?

31:06.265 --> 31:08.968
- Look, that Chuck
yesterday was old Chuck.

31:09.035 --> 31:10.436
This is new Chuck.

31:10.502 --> 31:12.671
And new Chuck would
drop anything for you.

31:12.738 --> 31:15.741
- Hmm.
Why should I believe you now?

31:19.411 --> 31:21.480
- If it wasn't clear,

31:21.547 --> 31:24.516
I just ripped the Syracuse
football game ticket in half.

31:27.086 --> 31:28.754
- All right, come in.

31:31.023 --> 31:33.092
- Let's--let's go get
some hot chocolate.

31:33.159 --> 31:35.094
Your treat, come on.

31:35.161 --> 31:36.795
- No, no, no, no.

31:36.862 --> 31:40.132
Normally, this would be defeat,
but not for Snow Day Hal.

31:40.199 --> 31:41.567
I could still make
an impression.

31:41.633 --> 31:43.869
I just gotta, uh...
just gotta plan my next move.

31:43.936 --> 31:46.805
- Well, Chuck's in her house,
and you're not.

31:46.872 --> 31:48.907
- Wait, wait.

31:52.278 --> 31:53.512
I'm going to get
in her house, too.

31:53.579 --> 31:54.880
- Wait, Hal,
her house is that way.

31:54.947 --> 31:56.548
What is your freak--
it's just here.

31:56.615 --> 31:57.749
- You'll see.
- But it's--

31:57.816 --> 31:59.185
- Anything can
happen on a snow day.

31:59.251 --> 32:00.352
- Wait!
Wait!

32:00.419 --> 32:01.587
Shoes.
Lift.

32:01.653 --> 32:04.056
- Okay, quickly.
- Yeah.

32:04.123 --> 32:05.958
Who am I?
- You're my hero. Bye!

32:06.025 --> 32:07.559
- Bye.

32:07.626 --> 32:09.928
- Okay, guys, if we're going
to take down a living monster

32:09.996 --> 32:11.897
and get a second snow day,
these snowballs

32:11.964 --> 32:13.199
got to be packed tight.

32:13.265 --> 32:15.101
- Fine.

32:15.167 --> 32:17.569
- Lucky for us, Snowplowman
overposts on social media,

32:17.636 --> 32:19.305
so I know he's stopping
right around here from

32:19.371 --> 32:20.806
mid-morning until we break.

32:20.872 --> 32:22.741
- And I did a few
calculations to determine

32:22.808 --> 32:24.310
how the wind chill
factor might affect

32:24.376 --> 32:25.677
the arc of the snowball.

32:25.744 --> 32:26.745
- Ew, math.

32:26.812 --> 32:28.047
We're good.

32:28.114 --> 32:29.048
Wayne, you've got
a sling for us?

32:29.115 --> 32:30.382
- Right here.

32:30.449 --> 32:32.284
- [laughing]

32:32.351 --> 32:33.452
- Don't laugh at me.

32:33.519 --> 32:35.487
It's my grandma's, okay?

32:35.554 --> 32:37.123
It's the best I can
do on short notice.

32:37.189 --> 32:38.790
- Okay.

32:38.857 --> 32:40.059
Plan is to distract
him with the balls

32:40.126 --> 32:41.360
and then jab a hole
in one of his tires.

32:41.427 --> 32:42.461
- Brilliant.

32:42.528 --> 32:43.996
- Not the way to
go if you ask me.

32:44.063 --> 32:44.997
- We didn't.

32:45.064 --> 32:46.498
- Fine.

32:46.565 --> 32:48.000
Then you won't get to
hear my genius idea.

32:48.067 --> 32:49.135
- Good.

32:49.201 --> 32:50.202
- Sinkhole.

32:50.269 --> 32:51.537
- What's a sinkhole?

32:51.603 --> 32:53.305
- A cavity in the ground
caused by erosion.

32:53.372 --> 32:56.208
One does not simply
create a sinkhole.

32:56.275 --> 32:58.277
- Not with that attitude.

32:58.344 --> 33:02.148
[honking]

33:02.214 --> 33:03.882
- Snowplowman.

33:03.949 --> 33:07.453
[dramatic music]

33:07.519 --> 33:09.188
- Snowplowman, pull over!

33:09.255 --> 33:12.024
The sunlight is hitting us
at an ideal angle,

33:12.091 --> 33:15.994
and I would like to suggest
taking a commemorative selfie.

33:17.063 --> 33:18.564
- Great idea, Trudy.

33:18.630 --> 33:20.266
You know, they don't make
them like you anymore.

33:20.332 --> 33:22.000
- Actually, they do.

33:22.068 --> 33:24.903
I'm a standard artificial
intelligence device

33:24.970 --> 33:28.174
that you program to
remind you to eat, tell you

33:28.240 --> 33:30.176
that you're handsome...
- Hey.

33:30.242 --> 33:32.111
- You're not a disappointment
to your mother.

33:32.178 --> 33:33.312
- Okay, selfie time!

33:33.379 --> 33:35.281
- Mm-hmm.

33:35.347 --> 33:38.217
Cheese!

33:38.284 --> 33:39.251
[camera lens snaps]

33:39.318 --> 33:40.852
- Oh, that is a framer.

33:42.321 --> 33:45.357
* I love
clearing snow in winter *

33:45.424 --> 33:48.627
* And seeing the
pavement shine through *

33:48.694 --> 33:51.963
* I love driving
in a blizzard *

33:52.030 --> 33:55.134
* The cold
and my lips turning blue *

33:55.201 --> 33:58.904
* I love holiday movies
and acai smoothies *

33:58.970 --> 34:01.006
* And Trudy,
I love you to bits *

34:01.073 --> 34:02.574
- Aww.

34:02.641 --> 34:06.112
- * But I hate, hate, hate,
hate, hate these kids *

34:06.178 --> 34:08.746
* *

34:08.813 --> 34:11.917
* I love the thrill of
online shopping *

34:11.983 --> 34:14.786
* For gadgets
to spruce up my ride *

34:14.853 --> 34:18.623
* I love staying up
and watching the Tonys *

34:18.690 --> 34:20.792
* With Mom by my side *

34:20.859 --> 34:23.929
* I love small vegan cafes
and pumpkin spice lattes *

34:23.995 --> 34:26.697
* And a good social media
blitz *

34:26.764 --> 34:31.002
* But I hate, hate, hate,
hate, hate these kids *

34:31.069 --> 34:32.638
* *

34:32.704 --> 34:36.275
* At the first snowflake
of the season *

34:36.342 --> 34:39.545
* I shed a tear of joy *

34:39.610 --> 34:42.181
* A mission
that I can believe in *

34:42.248 --> 34:47.085
* To make sure
their dreams are destroyed! *

34:47.152 --> 34:50.021
* I love setting up
my playlist *

34:50.088 --> 34:53.024
* The ultimate
mega plow mix! *

34:53.091 --> 34:56.094
* I love my rising
social status *

34:56.161 --> 34:58.964
* And rocking
these customized kicks *

34:59.030 --> 35:02.434
* I love night vision cameras
and matching pajamas *

35:02.501 --> 35:05.003
* Love being the guy
who admits *

35:05.070 --> 35:09.575
* That I hate hate, hate,
hate, hate these kids *

35:09.641 --> 35:12.077
* *

35:12.144 --> 35:15.714
* This time of year
takes me right back *

35:15.781 --> 35:18.650
* To that fateful
snow day past *

35:18.717 --> 35:21.453
* I was only eight years old *

35:21.520 --> 35:24.523
* *

35:24.590 --> 35:27.426
* I had a brand new
snow plow toy *

35:27.493 --> 35:30.396
* Steering, racing,
so much joy *

35:30.462 --> 35:34.800
* I couldn't even
feel the cold *

35:34.866 --> 35:36.568
* Then they stuck up
from behind *

35:36.635 --> 35:38.069
* They ripped it from
my grasp *

35:38.136 --> 35:39.871
* They stole it--
gone forever! *

35:39.938 --> 35:41.973
* They pointed
and they laughed *

35:42.040 --> 35:46.812
* The rudest, meanest
gang of nasty kids *

35:46.878 --> 35:48.647
* From that day on *

35:48.714 --> 35:54.786
* I vowed to make them
suffer like I did *

35:54.853 --> 35:57.088
- Therapy appointment
scheduled Monday, 9:00 a.m.

35:57.155 --> 35:58.824
- Trudy, not now!

35:58.890 --> 36:01.793
* I love laughing
in their faces! *

36:01.860 --> 36:05.231
* Now it's my turn to be mean *

36:05.297 --> 36:10.569
* I love people of all ages,
except if they're under 18 *

36:10.636 --> 36:12.271
* I love having the power *

36:12.338 --> 36:16.275
* I know it's my hour to wipe
snow days right off the grid *

36:16.342 --> 36:19.978
* Because I hate, hate,
hate, hate, hate these *

36:20.045 --> 36:22.814
* Just can't tolerate these *

36:22.881 --> 36:28.186
* Hate, hate, hate,
hate, hate these kids! *

36:32.358 --> 36:33.959
- Okay, here he comes.

36:34.025 --> 36:35.927
Snowball me.
- Yes, my lady.

36:35.994 --> 36:37.829
- Wayne, get that sling ready.
- Eli, catch.

36:37.896 --> 36:38.997
- Got it.

36:40.566 --> 36:42.368
- Ah!

36:42.434 --> 36:44.035
Yeah!

36:44.102 --> 36:45.337
Snack time, Trudy.

36:45.404 --> 36:46.472
- Mm-mm.

36:46.538 --> 36:49.107
- Oh, my favorite, anchovies.

36:49.174 --> 36:50.342
- Very pungent.

36:50.409 --> 36:51.877
- You know where
you're going, huh?

36:51.943 --> 36:52.978
- [grunt]

36:53.044 --> 36:54.112
- Uhh--

36:54.179 --> 36:55.414
- Give me the piercer.

36:55.481 --> 36:57.082
Now throw, throw, throw!

36:59.217 --> 37:00.419
- Kids.

37:00.486 --> 37:02.554
- There they are!

37:02.621 --> 37:05.156
[suspenseful music]

37:05.223 --> 37:07.426
- Hey!
- Hey, children, stop that!

37:07.493 --> 37:09.361
- Stop it!
- Oh, you bad kids!

37:09.428 --> 37:11.263
- Knock it off! Hey!

37:11.330 --> 37:13.865
Oh, I'm gonna get you.

37:13.932 --> 37:16.234
Knock it off!
- Do something, Snowplowman!

37:16.302 --> 37:17.269
- Stop throwing!

37:17.336 --> 37:19.070
[air hissing]

37:22.207 --> 37:23.509
[groans]

37:25.377 --> 37:26.978
Flat tire, huh?

37:29.281 --> 37:31.216
[laughing]

37:35.987 --> 37:38.290
Trudy, activate mega cannon.

37:38.357 --> 37:39.257
- Activated!

37:40.826 --> 37:43.194
Here...we...go...

37:43.261 --> 37:45.631
- Snow in the hole!

37:46.865 --> 37:48.166
Scatter!

37:49.935 --> 37:51.903
Trudy, you got 'em targeted?
- Bull's-eye.

37:51.970 --> 37:53.805
- Hey, wait!
- We've gotta get out of here!

37:53.872 --> 37:55.441
- Nice try, kiddies.

37:55.507 --> 37:57.576
You ain't getting
no second snow day.

38:00.546 --> 38:02.714
- Nothing is a bigger
threat to fashion than snow.

38:02.781 --> 38:05.183
- Ugh!
Why can't you just be longer?

38:05.250 --> 38:07.085
- That's why I'm here
to officially

38:07.152 --> 38:10.456
#Rebeccamend you start your
early afternoon off with a...

38:10.522 --> 38:12.290
- Hey, babe.
- Butter's in the fridge.

38:12.358 --> 38:13.492
- Love you.

38:13.559 --> 38:14.526
- Chuck.

38:14.593 --> 38:15.861
- Yeah, babe.

38:15.927 --> 38:17.429
- Make sure the toaster
is plugged in.

38:17.496 --> 38:19.431
- Who's better than you?

38:20.065 --> 38:21.867
- This way,
you're gonna keep warm

38:21.933 --> 38:23.535
without having to
sacrifice your silhouette.

38:23.602 --> 38:25.303
- Claire!
Claire Bonner!

38:25.371 --> 38:28.774
- Um, I'm Rebecca,
Rebecca Menderson.

38:28.840 --> 38:31.343
- Uh, yeah, I know,
and-and letting me speak

38:31.410 --> 38:33.445
for a moment would be
my official #Rebeccamendation.

38:33.512 --> 38:35.547
- [gasp] That is trademarked!

38:35.614 --> 38:38.083
- Claire Bonner, hi.

38:38.149 --> 38:40.386
My name is--is Hal Brandston.

38:40.452 --> 38:43.121
You probably don't know me
other than yesterday's

38:43.188 --> 38:45.391
milkshake malfunction,
but I know you.

38:45.457 --> 38:48.494
I know that when you're
nervous, you eat candy corn.

38:48.560 --> 38:50.095
I know that you hate pickles.

38:50.161 --> 38:52.330
And I know that you love
to dance more than anything

38:52.398 --> 38:54.400
in the world.
- Okay, yeah, this is--

38:54.466 --> 38:55.734
this is great.

38:55.801 --> 38:57.002
This is really sweet
and all, but I'm

38:57.068 --> 38:58.770
going to have to
officially #Rebeccamend

38:58.837 --> 39:00.506
that you leave immediately,
or I'm going to call security.

39:00.572 --> 39:02.207
- Security?
- Security!

39:04.342 --> 39:06.011
Dad!

39:12.518 --> 39:15.353
- I still think a sinkhole
would be way more efficient.

39:15.421 --> 39:17.756
- I truly don't know how many
more times I can tolerate him

39:17.823 --> 39:19.491
saying the word "sinkhole."

39:19.558 --> 39:22.227
- Let's try this first and then
revisit sinkhole, okay, buddy?

39:22.293 --> 39:24.730
- Well, my grandma needs
this wig back by 4:00.

39:24.796 --> 39:27.198
She's not too happy that
I stole her bra either.

39:27.265 --> 39:29.134
- Snowplowman
is about 45 seconds away.

39:29.200 --> 39:30.469
- How do you know?

39:30.536 --> 39:31.637
- I took the liberty of
adding a tracking device

39:31.703 --> 39:33.805
to one of
the snowballs you launched.

39:33.872 --> 39:35.941
- Does this coat
make me look boxy?

39:36.007 --> 39:37.776
[honking]
- Shh!

39:37.843 --> 39:39.244
He's coming.

39:39.310 --> 39:41.146
Let's go!

39:43.549 --> 39:44.916
- Oh, no, is it snowing?

39:44.983 --> 39:46.351
My grandma's going
to kill me if she

39:46.418 --> 39:48.286
finds out I got her hat wet!
- Just get out there!

39:48.353 --> 39:49.988
I'm not taking that test.

39:51.457 --> 39:52.524
- Danger!
- Aah!

39:52.591 --> 39:53.792
- Stop!
- Danger!

39:53.859 --> 39:55.861
[both screaming]
Danger! Danger!

40:02.033 --> 40:04.703
- Lady!
Lady, are you okay?

40:04.770 --> 40:07.072
Lady, I'm sorry.
Are you hurt?

40:07.138 --> 40:09.074
Are you okay?
Are you--

40:09.140 --> 40:11.943
- You ought to be
ashamed of yourself!

40:12.010 --> 40:13.912
- Jeez, you pack some
heat right there.

40:13.979 --> 40:14.980
Listen, lady, I'm sorry--

40:15.046 --> 40:16.848
- My name is not lady.

40:16.915 --> 40:19.284
My name is Gillie Butler,
and I demand respect!

40:19.350 --> 40:21.386
- Okay, Gillie, sorry.

40:21.453 --> 40:23.121
You came out of nowhere.

40:23.188 --> 40:24.923
You're lucky I didn't
plow you over.

40:24.990 --> 40:26.725
- Find the keys.
Find the keys.

40:26.792 --> 40:27.893
- Yes, milady.

40:27.959 --> 40:29.495
- Intruder detected.

40:29.561 --> 40:30.762
- What is that?

40:30.829 --> 40:33.064
- I have half a mind
to call the police!

40:33.131 --> 40:34.365
- Hey!

40:34.432 --> 40:36.468
All right, let's just
put our purses down

40:36.535 --> 40:38.069
and leave the feds out of it!

40:38.136 --> 40:41.372
- I am Trudy, property of
the gorgeous snowplowman,

40:41.439 --> 40:45.010
who was potty trained at
a perfectly appropriate age.

40:45.076 --> 40:47.746
- I have 13 strong-bodied
sons that wouldn't mind

40:47.813 --> 40:49.347
teaching you a lesson.

40:49.414 --> 40:50.348
- All right--

40:50.415 --> 40:51.650
13 sons?

40:51.717 --> 40:52.818
- Mm-hmm.

40:52.884 --> 40:54.486
- Wait a second, Gillie.
[ahem]

40:54.553 --> 40:56.087
What year were you born?

40:56.154 --> 40:58.023
- Oh, 2008.
- Nah-yea--

40:58.990 --> 41:00.358
- Ow.
- You're a kid.

41:00.425 --> 41:01.860
[honk]

41:02.728 --> 41:04.896
Ah ha, ha, ha!

41:04.963 --> 41:06.765
You looking for these?

41:06.832 --> 41:08.534
- Grab the bird.
- With alacrity, madam.

41:08.600 --> 41:09.901
- Easy, easy.

41:09.968 --> 41:11.670
- Let's go. You're coming
with me. Get over here.

41:11.737 --> 41:12.671
- No.
No.

41:12.738 --> 41:13.872
- Come on.
Come on.

41:13.939 --> 41:15.073
- No.
- You're coming with me.

41:15.140 --> 41:17.142
Yeah, you stupid kids!

41:17.208 --> 41:18.877
You think you can trick me,
you stupid kid?

41:18.944 --> 41:20.411
Get up in there.
Go on.

41:20.478 --> 41:22.614
Get up.
Get up.

41:22.681 --> 41:25.116
Wait, where's my--
where's the--

41:25.183 --> 41:26.117
Trudy.

41:26.184 --> 41:27.352
Trudy!

41:27.418 --> 41:28.554
Where's...

41:28.620 --> 41:34.492
Trudyyyyyyy!

41:38.664 --> 41:39.831
- Hi, Hal.

41:39.898 --> 41:41.099
- Ugh!

41:41.166 --> 41:42.801
You know, someday
I'm gonna surprise you.

41:42.868 --> 41:44.302
- Oh, I'm sure you will.

41:44.369 --> 41:45.904
- Can you say that a
little less patronizing?

41:45.971 --> 41:48.006
- I don't think I can.

41:48.073 --> 41:50.041
- Hey, did you see me
on #Rebeccamendations?

41:50.108 --> 41:51.910
- You definitely
made an impression.

41:51.977 --> 41:55.513
- Then on to step two,
humiliate the boyfriend.

41:55.581 --> 41:57.482
- If you hate him, why did
you draw him so handsome?

41:57.549 --> 41:59.050
- Because he's a gosh
darn snack, Lane.

41:59.117 --> 42:00.952
I can't deny it any longer.
- Yeah.

42:01.019 --> 42:02.788
- Hey, Rebecca Menderson
was cool enough to let me know

42:02.854 --> 42:04.089
where Chuck and Claire
are going.

42:04.155 --> 42:05.156
- And?
- You're going to love it.

42:05.223 --> 42:06.357
- [gasp] It's the
ice skating rink?

42:06.424 --> 42:07.726
- Ding, ding, ding.
- Yes, finally!

42:07.793 --> 42:08.894
- Here we go.
Let's go.

42:08.960 --> 42:10.729
- Wait, Hal, shoes!
- Oh!

42:10.796 --> 42:12.330
Ugh.
- [laughing]

42:12.397 --> 42:14.399
- I'm just--I'm just
making a snow angel.

42:14.465 --> 42:16.067
I did that totally on purpose.
- Uh-huh.

42:16.134 --> 42:18.203
Yeah.
- Yeah, yeah.

42:22.440 --> 42:24.342
- You know, snow angels
are great and all,

42:24.409 --> 42:27.278
but they kind of
break your heart.

42:27.345 --> 42:28.680
- How come?

42:28.747 --> 42:30.315
- Because it's all perfect,
but then you ruin it

42:30.381 --> 42:33.018
with your handprint
when you get up to look at it.

42:33.084 --> 42:35.220
- Yeah, true.

42:35.286 --> 42:39.324
Hey, why do you love
ice skating so much?

42:40.592 --> 42:42.160
- Honestly?

42:42.227 --> 42:43.494
- Yeah.

42:43.561 --> 42:44.562
- No.

42:44.630 --> 42:45.731
No, you'll think it's dumb.

42:45.797 --> 42:48.634
- No, I won't.

42:48.700 --> 42:49.901
- Okay.

42:50.836 --> 42:52.971
When I'm ice skating...

42:55.406 --> 42:56.507
- What?

42:56.574 --> 42:57.542
- I don't know.

42:57.609 --> 42:59.344
- Lane, it's just me.

43:00.879 --> 43:03.181
- Okay, fine.

43:03.248 --> 43:05.350
When I'm ice skating, I...

43:05.416 --> 43:06.652
[small laugh]

43:06.718 --> 43:10.521
I feel...beautiful.

43:11.790 --> 43:13.058
- Oh, that is dumb.

43:13.124 --> 43:14.592
- See? I told you--

43:14.660 --> 43:18.229
- No, it's dumb because
you're already beautiful.

43:18.296 --> 43:21.266
You're a beautiful girl,
Lane, like factually.

43:22.634 --> 43:24.703
Here, so you don't
ruin your snow angel

43:24.770 --> 43:26.872
with your handprint.

43:26.938 --> 43:28.506
- [grunts]

43:31.042 --> 43:32.210
- Perfect.

43:35.681 --> 43:36.815
[gasps]

43:36.882 --> 43:38.516
- You okay?

43:38.583 --> 43:39.617
- Yeah.

43:39.685 --> 43:42.654
Yeah, yeah, just,
you know, cold.

43:43.321 --> 43:48.026
- Oh, well, I know how
much you love this sweater.

43:48.093 --> 43:50.061
- No, no, no, no,
no, you'll be colder.

43:50.128 --> 43:52.363
Are you crazy?

43:52.430 --> 43:53.665
- Here.

43:53.732 --> 43:55.100
- Thanks.

43:55.166 --> 43:57.302
- Of course, let's go.
- Hal, wait.

43:57.368 --> 43:59.237
- What?

44:01.206 --> 44:02.974
- Did-did you do
something different

44:03.041 --> 44:04.642
with your hair today?

44:04.710 --> 44:07.946
- Oh, no, I can assure you
this mess is whatever it is.

44:08.013 --> 44:09.014
Let's go.

44:09.080 --> 44:10.315
- I'll meet you there.

44:10.381 --> 44:11.783
I just got to call
home real quick.

44:11.850 --> 44:13.551
- Okay.
- Okay.

