* *

46:57.916 --> 46:58.816
- Too pancakey.

46:58.884 --> 47:00.551
- Ugh!

47:00.618 --> 47:04.722
- Sheriff Randy,
we have made you 14 pancakes!

47:04.789 --> 47:07.325
- We can't count that first
abomination as a pancake.

47:07.392 --> 47:10.128
- We have made
you 13 pancakes

47:10.195 --> 47:12.730
that are either too dry,
too sweet, too gooey,

47:12.797 --> 47:14.365
or too pancakey.

47:14.432 --> 47:16.201
- People at work
are going to be really mad

47:16.267 --> 47:17.468
at Mommy and Daddy.

47:17.535 --> 47:18.937
- That sounds like
a you problem,

47:19.004 --> 47:20.571
not a me problem.

47:20.638 --> 47:22.240
- Oh, I say it
on one phone call,

47:22.307 --> 47:24.409
and he locks it in.

47:24.475 --> 47:25.476
- Hi, Mom and Dad.
- Natalie, Natalie!

47:25.543 --> 47:26.912
- No time to stop and chat!

47:26.978 --> 47:27.946
- Natalie, sweetie, sweetie!
We got a problem here!

47:28.013 --> 47:29.414
We're handcuffed together!

47:29.480 --> 47:31.016
Randy took those handcuffs,
and we're going crazy.

47:31.082 --> 47:33.118
It's a nightmare.

47:36.387 --> 47:37.688
- We are tickety boo.

47:37.755 --> 47:38.856
- Tickety boo?

47:38.924 --> 47:40.658
- Yes, tickety boo.
- Tickety boo?

47:40.725 --> 47:42.327
We're working here.
English, please.

47:42.393 --> 47:43.494
- It means we're good to go,

47:43.561 --> 47:45.530
and it was actually
quite English.

47:45.596 --> 47:47.698
[electronic chime]
- Whoa!

47:47.765 --> 47:50.068
- [crying]
They took my special bird.

47:50.135 --> 47:51.402
They took Trudy.

47:51.469 --> 47:53.471
[phone ringing]
Don't answer that!

47:53.538 --> 47:54.805
- It could be about Trudy.

47:54.872 --> 47:57.042
- Well, answer it,
for God's sake!

47:57.108 --> 47:58.576
- [sighs]

47:58.643 --> 48:00.378
Wayne Castle.
What's your hassle?

48:00.445 --> 48:02.213
[keyboard clicking]

48:02.280 --> 48:04.849
- Hello, Snowplowman.

48:04.916 --> 48:07.152
- Give me that!

48:07.218 --> 48:09.454
Trudy, baby, I miss you.

48:09.520 --> 48:12.523
- Say, "It's very
difficult being apart."

48:12.590 --> 48:15.961
- It's very difficult,
being a fart.

48:16.027 --> 48:17.095
- [sniggering]

48:17.162 --> 48:18.729
- Eli!
- Apologies.

48:18.796 --> 48:21.632
- Apart.
It's difficult being apart.

48:21.699 --> 48:23.434
- Trudy,
ask them what they want!

48:23.501 --> 48:25.903
I'll give them anything
to get you back.

48:25.971 --> 48:28.239
- Hey, watch the drumsticks!

48:28.306 --> 48:30.075
$1 million.

48:30.141 --> 48:31.409
both: What?

48:31.476 --> 48:32.910
- Worth a shot.

48:32.978 --> 48:34.079
[quirky mysterious music]

48:34.145 --> 48:35.746
- Easy, easy.

48:35.813 --> 48:38.549
Just kidding.
Ha, ha, ha.

48:38.616 --> 48:41.852
Bring the boy to the
center of town in one hour,

48:41.919 --> 48:44.355
or I will tell everyone
that you sleep with dollies!

48:44.422 --> 48:48.093
- [chuckling] Hey, Trudy,
that's private, okay?

48:48.159 --> 48:50.928
- I just made that up.

48:50.996 --> 48:52.297
- [chuckles]

48:52.363 --> 48:55.266
[upbeat music]

48:55.333 --> 49:02.607
* *

49:03.008 --> 49:04.209
- Hey.
- Hi.

49:04.275 --> 49:05.876
- Looking good, babe.
- Thanks.

49:05.943 --> 49:07.345
- Hey.
- Hey!

49:07.412 --> 49:09.314
- Oh, nice.
Your friends.

49:09.380 --> 49:10.481
Hey, I should get
to know them better

49:10.548 --> 49:12.350
so I can feel closer to you.

49:12.417 --> 49:13.651
- I appreciate that, Chuck.

49:13.718 --> 49:15.820
- What are their names again?

49:15.886 --> 49:18.056
- Hmm.

49:18.123 --> 49:20.391
Mason, Rebecca, and Missy.

49:20.458 --> 49:22.293
- Oof.
Never going to remember those.

49:22.360 --> 49:23.361
- Hey, you two.

49:23.428 --> 49:24.829
- Hey.
- You two.

49:24.895 --> 49:26.031
all: So...

49:26.097 --> 49:27.898
- Are Claire and Chuck
back together?

49:27.965 --> 49:29.834
- Like back-back?
- Together-together?

49:29.900 --> 49:33.771
- Correction, Claire and
new Chuck are back together.

49:33.838 --> 49:35.940
- Well, new Chuck
is on probation.

49:36.007 --> 49:37.908
- New Chuck does not know
what that word means.

49:37.975 --> 49:39.410
- It means
you better watch your back.

49:39.477 --> 49:41.079
- Watch your back.

49:41.146 --> 49:43.814
- And wash your back even
though it's hard to reach.

49:43.881 --> 49:44.749
- Missy.
- Babe.

49:44.815 --> 49:46.084
- I use a loofah on a stick.

49:46.151 --> 49:47.785
- What are you talking about,
Claire's friends?

49:47.852 --> 49:49.854
- We're talking
about Hal Brandston.

49:49.920 --> 49:51.022
- Guys.

49:51.089 --> 49:52.390
- Who's Hal Brandston?

49:52.457 --> 49:54.525
- Hal Brandston interrupted
my livestream

49:54.592 --> 49:55.960
to proclaim his love for Claire

49:56.027 --> 49:58.229
while I was officially
#Rebeccamending

49:58.296 --> 49:59.564
a light pant
for the transition

49:59.630 --> 50:01.532
from early afternoon
to mid-afternoon.

50:01.599 --> 50:03.101
- Well, I feel like an idiot.

50:03.168 --> 50:05.170
- Oh, Chuck, come on.
I don't even know that guy.

50:05.236 --> 50:06.737
- No, look at me.

50:06.804 --> 50:08.306
I should have gone
with a light pant.

50:08.373 --> 50:10.108
I'm going to go home
and change.

50:10.175 --> 50:12.310
- Chuck!
- Oh, angry voice.

50:12.377 --> 50:14.445
Our cue to exit.
[all chuckling]

50:15.446 --> 50:16.947
- I'm hungry.

50:17.014 --> 50:19.650
- I'm Germany
and like an eighth Scotland.

50:19.717 --> 50:21.419
- Mm-hmm.

50:21.486 --> 50:24.021
- Oh, hungry, like for food.

50:24.089 --> 50:25.223
- Yeah.
- I'm on it.

50:25.290 --> 50:26.157
- Mm-hmm?
- I'm on it.

50:26.224 --> 50:27.192
- Okay.

50:27.258 --> 50:28.659
[mysterious music]

50:28.726 --> 50:30.228
- Okay, he just said he's going
to get Claire some food.

50:30.295 --> 50:32.029
You ready?
- I guess.

50:32.097 --> 50:33.364
- Come on!

50:33.431 --> 50:34.399
Hey, you've already done
the impossible today.

50:34.465 --> 50:35.700
- [chuckles]
What do you mean?

50:35.766 --> 50:38.169
- You look cute
in the ugly sweater.

50:38.236 --> 50:39.604
- [laughs]

50:49.714 --> 50:51.216
- You're Lane from school.

50:51.282 --> 50:53.518
- And you're Dirk from school.

50:53.584 --> 50:54.985
- You know me?

50:55.052 --> 50:57.555
- Of course I do.
[giggles]

50:57.622 --> 50:59.090
- Lane, I've always wanted
to tell you something--

50:59.157 --> 51:01.192
- Oh, my God, there's a spider
on your shirt!

51:01.259 --> 51:02.527
- What? Where?
I hate spiders!

51:02.593 --> 51:03.728
- Now it's on your hat!

51:03.794 --> 51:05.096
- [screaming]
- Oh, it's on your apron!

51:05.163 --> 51:06.631
Take it off! Take it off!
- No! No! Did I get it?

51:06.697 --> 51:08.333
- Oh, no,
it crawled off your neck!

51:08.399 --> 51:11.936
Run, Dirk, run!
- [screams]

51:12.002 --> 51:14.472
- [giggles]

51:14.539 --> 51:15.773
- Does anyone work here?

51:15.840 --> 51:17.275
Some of us have
hungry girlfriends.

51:17.342 --> 51:19.277
- Coming, coming.

51:19.344 --> 51:20.478
Sorry for the delay, folks.

51:20.545 --> 51:22.413
Nasty pest issue back there.

51:22.480 --> 51:24.382
- Mm. Mm-mm.

51:24.449 --> 51:27.652
- Hey there.
- Hey, uh, Dirk.

51:27.718 --> 51:30.087
- It's a family name.
- Oh.

51:30.155 --> 51:32.323
So what do girls, like, eat?

51:32.390 --> 51:33.891
- Hmm, what do girls,
like, eat?

51:33.958 --> 51:36.827
Mm, you know,
girls are complicated.

51:36.894 --> 51:38.028
- Right?

51:38.095 --> 51:39.497
- You know what
you can't go wrong with?

51:39.564 --> 51:41.499
- What?
- A burger with pickles.

51:41.566 --> 51:42.567
- Pickles?

51:42.633 --> 51:45.836
- She is going to love it.

51:45.903 --> 51:48.606
- You're going to love it.
- Oh, I'm starving.

51:48.673 --> 51:51.242
What'd you get me?
- Just trust.

51:51.309 --> 51:52.910
- Okay.

51:53.844 --> 51:55.480
Mm, mm.

51:59.517 --> 52:00.551
Does this have pickles?

52:00.618 --> 52:01.686
- Extra pickles.

52:01.752 --> 52:04.922
- [gagging and spitting]

52:04.989 --> 52:06.191
I hate pickles.

52:06.257 --> 52:09.160
I've told you this
like a million times.

52:09.227 --> 52:11.562
- Dirk.
- Who's Dirk?

52:11.629 --> 52:13.631
- She's the cute girl
who works at the food truck.

52:13.698 --> 52:15.666
- Cute girl?
- Yeah.

52:15.733 --> 52:17.768
- Okay, that's it.
We're done.

52:17.835 --> 52:19.904
- Wait, Claire.
- Like for real this time.

52:19.970 --> 52:21.572
- Claire, come on.

52:21.639 --> 52:25.676
Claire, you're so much cuter
than her.

52:25.743 --> 52:27.077
- Ugh!
- Are you okay?

52:27.144 --> 52:29.079
- What happened?
- Where's Chuck going?

52:31.882 --> 52:33.150
- Whoo!

52:33.218 --> 52:35.686
Okay, so I think step two
went off without a hitch.

52:35.753 --> 52:37.422
- Oh, hi!
- [laughs]

52:37.488 --> 52:39.690
- You are amazing!
- [laughs]

52:39.757 --> 52:42.026
- [sighs]
Okay.

52:42.092 --> 52:44.862
Time for step three,
the grand gesture.

52:44.929 --> 52:46.431
This step requires
actually talking to her,

52:46.497 --> 52:48.533
so excuse me while I panic.

52:48.599 --> 52:50.601
- Hal, you know you don't have
to do this much

52:50.668 --> 52:52.069
for a girl to like you.
- Yes, I do.

52:52.136 --> 52:56.173
- Trust me, you don't.
Regular Hal isn't so bad.

52:56.241 --> 53:00.545
I mean, sure, you're a little
awkward, but you're also--

53:00.611 --> 53:03.581
[soft dramatic music]

53:03.648 --> 53:04.749
Do you remember
in second grade,

53:04.815 --> 53:06.784
we went on the field trip
to the zoo?

53:06.851 --> 53:08.953
- Oh, the whooping cranes.
- [laughs] Yes!

53:09.019 --> 53:11.789
I was so irrationally scared
and started freaking out,

53:11.856 --> 53:13.824
but before the other kids
could make fun of me,

53:13.891 --> 53:15.993
you started saying,
"Whoop, whoop! I'm a crane!

53:16.060 --> 53:18.162
Whoop, whoop!"
over and over.

53:18.229 --> 53:19.697
- That was so embarrassing.

53:19.764 --> 53:21.399
- So embarrassing.
[laughs]

53:21.466 --> 53:27.104
But it distracted everyone
from me and also distracted me.

53:27.171 --> 53:29.474
You were my hero.

53:29.540 --> 53:35.380
Point is, you were enough then,
and you're enough now.

53:35.446 --> 53:38.649
* *

53:38.716 --> 53:40.951
- Hey, Claire.

53:42.887 --> 53:45.890
Meet me at the soccer field
in an hour?

53:45.956 --> 53:46.824
- Should I?

53:46.891 --> 53:48.293
- I mean, he's kind of cute.

53:48.359 --> 53:49.727
- And it would be a great way
to get back at Chuck.

53:49.794 --> 53:51.996
- [chuckling]
Chuck is so hot.

53:52.062 --> 53:53.598
- Missy, think before you talk.

53:53.664 --> 53:54.599
- Babe, you need
to get with the program.

53:54.665 --> 53:56.701
- Okay!
- [sighs] Yes!

53:56.767 --> 53:57.735
Oh, God, it's happening.

53:57.802 --> 54:01.772
- Oh, shoes! Okay, lift.
Who am I?

54:01.839 --> 54:05.276
- You're my hero.
Like, for real.

54:05.343 --> 54:07.144
- [chuckles softly]

54:07.211 --> 54:13.684
* *

54:13.751 --> 54:16.887
- Johnny Depp-uty?

54:16.954 --> 54:19.223
- Oh, yes.

54:19.290 --> 54:20.291
Good call, babe.
- [laughs]

54:20.358 --> 54:21.459
- Very smart.
- Thank you.

54:21.526 --> 54:23.093
- Yeah.
Okay, here we go.

54:23.160 --> 54:25.763
- Okay.
- Three, two, one...

54:25.830 --> 54:27.465
flip.
- 'Ey!

54:27.532 --> 54:30.000
- Pretty good.
That's really good.

54:32.337 --> 54:35.406
- Hey.

54:35.473 --> 54:37.475
I've missed you.

54:37.542 --> 54:39.744
- I've missed you, too.

54:39.810 --> 54:42.813
- Do my ears detect nostalgia?

54:42.880 --> 54:45.483
- Sorry, Johnny Depp-uty.

54:45.550 --> 54:46.917
[both groan softly]

54:46.984 --> 54:48.152
You know what I think we need?

54:48.218 --> 54:50.621
- No, three kids is enough.
- [laughs]

54:50.688 --> 54:55.693
I'm thinking we need
a little powdered sugar.

54:55.760 --> 54:57.294
- Oh, you want to go
with the powdered sugar?

54:57.362 --> 54:58.563
- Mm-hmm.

54:58.629 --> 55:00.931
- Okay, how about
there, there, there?

55:00.998 --> 55:02.633
No, see, this is how it starts.

55:02.700 --> 55:04.201
We're going to get
ourselves into trouble.

55:04.268 --> 55:05.870
- Johnny Depp-uty.

55:05.936 --> 55:09.474
- Here we go.
Your pancakes, sir.

55:09.540 --> 55:12.076
[dramatic orchestral music]

55:12.142 --> 55:13.511
- [clears throat]

55:13.578 --> 55:20.718
* *

55:25.723 --> 55:29.660
- Now that is
perfectly pancakey!

55:29.727 --> 55:31.896
- Ah, yes, yes!
- Oh!

55:31.962 --> 55:34.932
- That's great news.
Can you please uncuff us now?

55:34.999 --> 55:37.201
- First, you gotta catch me!

55:37.267 --> 55:38.403
- Oh!

55:38.469 --> 55:40.505
- Randy!
- Randy!

55:40.571 --> 55:41.739
- Randy.

55:43.474 --> 55:45.009
I'm hit!

55:45.075 --> 55:47.111
[groaning]

55:47.177 --> 55:48.813
- Don't you die on me, soldier!

55:48.879 --> 55:51.015
- I'm so cold....so cold.

55:51.081 --> 55:52.883
- Oh!
- [chuckles]

55:52.950 --> 55:55.586
- Oh, you're going down, son!

55:55.653 --> 55:56.821
* *

55:56.887 --> 55:59.990
[horn blasting]

56:04.061 --> 56:07.164
[western duel music]

56:07.231 --> 56:14.171
* *

57:01.285 --> 57:03.387
- [blows nose]

57:03.454 --> 57:04.655
[sniffles]
Blah.

57:04.722 --> 57:07.592
- [cracks neck]

57:07.658 --> 57:10.528
[tense musical crescendo]

57:10.595 --> 57:17.735
* *

57:27.044 --> 57:30.280
[tense music fading]

57:30.347 --> 57:31.448
- Give me my bird.

57:31.516 --> 57:32.750
- I'll give you your bird

57:32.817 --> 57:34.652
if you promise to stop plowing.

57:34.719 --> 57:36.386
- Not a chance.

57:36.453 --> 57:37.722
- [sighs]

57:37.788 --> 57:39.824
- Hey. What are you doing?
Don't, don't.

57:39.890 --> 57:42.159
What--how? Don't you--
[wailing unintelligibly]

57:42.226 --> 57:44.995
Why would you hurt her?
She's done nothing!

57:45.062 --> 57:47.064
- Psst, Wayne.
Wayne, my boy.

57:47.131 --> 57:48.365
Here.

57:48.432 --> 57:49.600
- What are these for?

57:49.667 --> 57:51.135
- You're going to cut off
the accelerator

57:51.201 --> 57:54.038
so the snowplow can't move.

57:54.104 --> 57:55.673
- He'll be totally stuck here.

57:55.740 --> 57:58.008
- Precisely.
- Oh!

57:58.075 --> 57:59.944
You're smarter than you look.

58:01.679 --> 58:05.482
- Give me my bird, or you'll
never see your friend again.

58:05.550 --> 58:06.717
He'll live with me,

58:06.784 --> 58:09.086
and I'll make him
trim my mom's toenails!

58:09.153 --> 58:10.354
- Ew.

58:10.420 --> 58:11.822
- Oh, yeah, they're filthy!
It's gross!

58:11.889 --> 58:13.558
[upbeat suspenseful music]

58:13.624 --> 58:15.359
- You know what, Snowplowman?

58:15.425 --> 58:18.062
I'm an adorable
and precocious young lady

58:18.128 --> 58:20.297
with my whole life ahead of me.

58:20.364 --> 58:23.834
You, well, you're just
an ugly mug with mommy issues

58:23.901 --> 58:25.603
who's in love with a toy bird.

58:25.670 --> 58:27.237
- She has a name!

58:27.304 --> 58:32.509
- Look, I'll let you win today
because I know I win at life.

58:33.477 --> 58:34.912
- Oh, Trudy.

58:34.979 --> 58:36.313
Trudy,
did the bad girl hurt you?

58:36.380 --> 58:38.315
[smooching]

58:38.382 --> 58:40.050
- Gross.

58:40.117 --> 58:41.786
- It's called love, okay?

58:41.852 --> 58:43.153
And you know what, girlie?

58:43.220 --> 58:45.322
You're coming with me!
- No! Hey!

58:45.389 --> 58:46.924
- Yeah, you just--
- Stranger danger!

58:46.991 --> 58:48.292
Get your hands off of me!
- You're coming with me.

58:48.358 --> 58:50.628
- You shall not separate me
from my queen!

58:50.695 --> 58:52.162
- Get up in there.

58:52.229 --> 58:55.265
- I demand that you get
your filthy hands off her!

58:55.332 --> 58:56.901
- Get in there.
Come on, let's go!

58:56.967 --> 59:00.304
That's right.
Oh, Trudy, Trudy.

59:00.370 --> 59:01.471
Here you go, baby.

59:01.538 --> 59:02.940
- Boom, boom!

59:03.007 --> 59:04.975
- Oh, I'm going to make
you three ragamuffins watch

59:05.042 --> 59:07.878
while I plow through your
dreams of a second snow day.

59:07.945 --> 59:09.113
Trudy, start the engine.

59:09.179 --> 59:11.015
- Starting engine.

59:11.081 --> 59:12.917
- Let's blow
this Popsicle stand.

59:12.983 --> 59:15.019
- Exiting Popsicle stand.

59:15.085 --> 59:16.854
[engine chugging]

59:16.921 --> 59:18.355
- Wayne.

59:18.422 --> 59:21.225
[horn blasts]

59:21.291 --> 59:24.629
- Oh, that's the gas pedal.

59:24.695 --> 59:26.496
[pedal thunking]
- Hey.

59:26.563 --> 59:29.033
Hey!
What's going on with my brakes?

59:29.099 --> 59:31.936
[all screaming]

59:34.104 --> 59:38.609
- Okay, Hal Brandston.
[chuckles]

59:38.676 --> 59:40.244
What's going on?

59:42.847 --> 59:44.281
- Claire.
[clears throat]

59:44.348 --> 59:49.720
Claire, I--I have spent
half my life pining for you.

59:49.787 --> 59:51.622
Isn't that ridiculous?

59:51.689 --> 59:54.491
I mean, if you feel something
wonderful for someone,

59:54.558 --> 59:56.593
shouldn't you tell them?

59:56.661 --> 1:00:01.165
So here I am, not just
telling you, but showing you.

1:00:01.231 --> 1:00:02.432
This is my grand gesture.

1:00:02.499 --> 1:00:06.737
I just--
hopefully, it's not too late.

1:00:06.804 --> 1:00:09.674
[delicate dramatic music]

1:00:09.740 --> 1:00:15.713
* *

1:00:15.780 --> 1:00:18.482
- Is it a whale?

1:00:18.548 --> 1:00:19.784
- Yeah.

1:00:19.850 --> 1:00:22.987
I, um--I thought you
might be missing this.

1:00:23.053 --> 1:00:28.225
* *

1:00:28.292 --> 1:00:29.626
- Where did you find this?

1:00:29.694 --> 1:00:33.097
[engine revving]

1:00:33.163 --> 1:00:36.533
[rock music]

1:00:36.600 --> 1:00:43.774
* *

1:00:44.474 --> 1:00:46.410
Chuck, don't bother.
- Wait. I know I messed up.

1:00:46.476 --> 1:00:47.745
- Chuck, no.

1:00:47.812 --> 1:00:49.279
- When I looked up this
Hal Brandston clown

1:00:49.346 --> 1:00:51.048
in the yearbook, he's never
even been on a sports team,

1:00:51.115 --> 1:00:52.649
like not even a fake sport
like golf.

1:00:52.717 --> 1:00:53.818
- Now hold on a second.

1:00:53.884 --> 1:00:55.219
- My point is
I'm Chuck Wheeler,

1:00:55.285 --> 1:00:56.620
and you're Claire Bonner.

1:00:56.687 --> 1:00:57.988
The Chucks and the Claires
of the world

1:00:58.055 --> 1:01:00.024
always end up together.

1:01:00.090 --> 1:01:01.091
- Not on a snow day.

1:01:01.158 --> 1:01:02.693
- What'd you say?
[Claire gasps]

1:01:04.862 --> 1:01:07.031
- Meet me at the theater.
- Okay!

1:01:07.097 --> 1:01:09.066
[dramatic music]

1:01:09.133 --> 1:01:10.434
- You're toast, Brandston!

1:01:10.500 --> 1:01:12.436
[engine revving]

1:01:12.502 --> 1:01:15.672
* *

1:01:15.740 --> 1:01:18.442
Yeah, you better run!

1:01:18.508 --> 1:01:20.510
[horn blasting]

1:01:20.577 --> 1:01:22.412
- Have you ever driven
without brakes before?

1:01:22.479 --> 1:01:23.513
- No!

1:01:23.580 --> 1:01:24.882
- Well, can you
drive any slower?

1:01:24.949 --> 1:01:26.283
- [high-pitched
No!

1:01:26.350 --> 1:01:27.818
- Well, how much longer
until the gas runs out?

1:01:27.885 --> 1:01:29.586
- [normally] Oh, about two
hours unless we hit a building

1:01:29.653 --> 1:01:32.522
or fall off a cliff because
you won't stop distracting me!

1:01:32.589 --> 1:01:33.991
* *

1:01:34.058 --> 1:01:36.360
- I can't believe
you cut the brakes.

1:01:36.426 --> 1:01:38.028
- I can't believe
you said no to sinkholes!

1:01:38.095 --> 1:01:39.696
- I still say no to sinkholes!

1:01:39.764 --> 1:01:41.031
All you do is sit there

1:01:41.098 --> 1:01:43.633
in your huge, stupid,
puffy grandma coat

1:01:43.700 --> 1:01:44.902
saying sinkholes, sinkholes,
sinkholes!

1:01:44.969 --> 1:01:46.636
- It's not that huge!

1:01:46.703 --> 1:01:49.073
- A plane could perform
an emergency landing on you.

1:01:49.139 --> 1:01:51.108
[soft energetic music]

1:01:51.175 --> 1:01:53.343
which is exactly
what we're going to do.

1:01:53.410 --> 1:01:54.812
- What?

1:01:54.879 --> 1:01:57.114
- Three inches of down
under the coat, ten-foot drop.

1:01:57.181 --> 1:01:58.949
- What are you doing?
- Math.

1:01:59.016 --> 1:02:00.517
- Oh, my God, it is useful!

1:02:00.584 --> 1:02:02.252
- Trudy, how fast
are we traveling?

1:02:02.319 --> 1:02:03.854
- 41 miles per hour.

1:02:03.921 --> 1:02:05.489
- Don't talk to my bird!

1:02:05.555 --> 1:02:06.924
- Carry the two.

1:02:06.991 --> 1:02:07.958
Yes!

1:02:08.025 --> 1:02:09.459
* *

1:02:09.526 --> 1:02:12.696
[all screaming]
- Danger, danger!

1:02:12.763 --> 1:02:13.931
[dramatic music]

1:02:13.998 --> 1:02:15.966
- [screams]

1:02:16.033 --> 1:02:17.234
- [shouts]

1:02:17.301 --> 1:02:19.003
- Wayne, old buddy, old pal.

1:02:19.069 --> 1:02:21.005
- You're not landing on me!

1:02:21.071 --> 1:02:22.372
- Fine!
Question, though.

1:02:22.439 --> 1:02:23.941
Do you want to be the guy
that cut the wrong wire

1:02:24.008 --> 1:02:26.777
or the guy that saved the day?

1:02:26.844 --> 1:02:28.846
- Fine!
Climb aboard.

1:02:28.913 --> 1:02:31.348
- Grab on, Eli!
- Ready as always, my lady!

1:02:31.415 --> 1:02:33.383
- What are you doing?
Shut that door!

1:02:33.450 --> 1:02:34.785
- One, two, three!
- No, wait!

1:02:34.852 --> 1:02:36.353
- [shouts]
Oof!

1:02:38.188 --> 1:02:41.125
- [shouting]

1:02:41.191 --> 1:02:43.360
[Snowplowman and Trudy scream]

1:02:43.427 --> 1:02:45.695
all: Oh!

1:02:45.762 --> 1:02:49.666
- Whoa!
- Whoa!

1:02:49.733 --> 1:02:55.505
* *

1:02:55.572 --> 1:02:59.409
all: Whoa!

1:03:12.089 --> 1:03:14.925
- Is the snow plow--
- Sinking?

1:03:14.992 --> 1:03:18.762
- Yes!
Sinkhole!

